My point is that if you&#x27;re going to iterate through the entire dictionary, there should be a way to get full key-value pairs, so you don&#x27;t have to look up the value for each key. There&#x27;s no need to change the entire example. Something like this:<p><pre><code>        for ((name, job) in people) {
          trace(&#x27;$name does $job for a living!&#x27;);
        }</code></pre>
